8a3eb-34 | 2026-06-17T23:34:44Z | session:8a3eb1b2-7bbf-4761-ad1a-411a0a1fa666 | ### The Three Sacred Roles (strictly separated) \n  \n ``` \n Subscribe  →  Orchestrate  →  Execute \n (relay)       (runtime)        (tenex-agent) \n ``` \n  \n - **Subscribe**: The relay connection and event fan-out. In production today this is `tenex daemon` (the supervisor). Roadmap: a dedicated `tenex relay-mux` process. \n - **Orchestrate** (`tenex runtime`, per-project): Dispatch, RAL state, delegation routing, delegation registry, message injection, kill-switch registry. Never calls LLMs. \n - **Execute** (`tenex-agent`, one-shot per conversation-turn): The LLM/tool loop. Reads one Nostr event from stdin, runs the iterative rig loop, emits signed NDJSON frames to stdout. **Never opens a relay connection.** \n 
