:"admitted"} or Acl{action:"blocked"} \n - `handle_incoming` (inbound Mention to hosted agent) → Msg (inbound) \n - `handle_incoming` (Status envelope) → Status (with dedup) \n - `handle_incoming` (Profile envelope) → Profile (first-seen dedup) \n - `handle_incoming` (Presence envelope, first-seen) → Join (via peer_sessions map) \n - `spawn_pruner` (sessions dropped from DB) → Leave \n  \n JOIN/LEAVE + SUPPRESSION \n  \n Join/Leave have no relay round-trip. An in-memory `peer_sessions: Mutex<HashMap<String, PeerTracked>>` on DaemonState tracks `{first_seen, project, slug, host}` keyed by session_id. When a Presence envelope arrives: if session_id is not in the map, emit Join and insert; subsequent beats are silent. When the pruner sweeps, it calls `list_peer_sessions(None, before)` to get the still-alive set after the DB prune, then emits Leave for every session that was in the map but is not in the post-prune live set, removing them from the map. \n  \n Profile dedup: `seen_profiles: Mutex<HashSet<String>>` — first pubkey occurrence emits Profile, repeats are dropped. \n Status dedup: `last_status: Mutex<HashMap<(String,String),String>>` keyed by (pubkey, project) — only emits when the status string differs from the last-seen value. \n  \n NEW CLI FLAGS (17 total on `tail` subcommand) \n  \n | Flag | Effect | \n |------|--------| \n | `--project <slug>` | scope to one project | \n | `--agent <slug>` | filter by agent | \n | `--host <host>` | filter by host | \n | `--since <spec>` | backfill start (unix ts or 1h/30m/2d/60s) | \n | `--backfill <n>` | limit backfill messages (default 50) | \n | `--only <cat,...>` | whitelist categories | \n | `--exclude <cat,...>` | blacklist categories | \n | `--include <cat,...>` | add back excluded | \n | `--all` | min_tier = noise (everything) | \n | `--compact` | no project/host annotations | \n | `--relative` | relative timestamps | \n | `--no-emoji` | ASCII fallbacks | \n | `--no-color` | strip ANSI (also respects NO_COLOR env)